#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:14
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can estimate your \\textbf{minimal} play time using the following formula:\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\\begin{center}\n"
"  Play Time $= \\boldsymbol{P × R × 5}$ [min]\n"
"\\end{center}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Where:\n"
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item[$\\textbf{P}$] -- number of players\n"
"  \\item[$\\textbf{R}$] -- number of rounds\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols
#: sections/recommendations.tex:29
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Therefore, if you're playing a 3-player scenario consisting of 12 rounds, you can easily calculate that $3 × 12 × 5 = 180$.\n"
"Your expected minimal play time should be around 3 hours.\n"
"To calculate the \\textbf{upper bound} of your play time (more realistic if there are inexperienced players), simply double the result.\n"
"So in this case that would be 6 hours.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

